00:47:53.890 --> 00:47:56.411
So there's no longer any connection

00:47:56.411 --> 00:47:58.971
from that computer to my computer.

00:48:00.450 --> 00:48:01.291
And-

00:48:01.291 --> 00:48:02.971
Connected to an intermediary.

00:48:02.971 --> 00:48:03.810
Yes.

00:48:03.810 --> 00:48:06.851
And like very concretely, if you follow this,

00:48:06.851 --> 00:48:07.731
you will get it.

00:48:07.731 --> 00:48:12.731
So if I just shut down the previous port,

00:48:13.411 --> 00:48:14.690
I'm going to get the previous daemons.

00:48:15.810 --> 00:48:19.051
And in this case, what I'm going to do

00:48:19.051 --> 00:48:22.771
is I'm going to create a local URL, right?

00:48:22.771 --> 00:48:27.771
So this is not the URL that's open

00:48:27.890 --> 00:48:29.570
to other computers on the network.

00:48:29.570 --> 00:48:31.570
This is a local URL.

00:48:31.570 --> 00:48:33.490
I'm going to set TCP equals true

00:48:33.490 --> 00:48:36.091
because this is a TCP connection.

00:48:36.690 --> 00:48:37.531
If I use status,

00:48:37.531 --> 00:48:40.171
this just gives me a little bit more information

00:48:40.171 --> 00:48:45.171
than info, but you can see we're actually listening

00:48:46.490 --> 00:48:48.731
to this 127, this address,

00:48:48.731 --> 00:48:49.971
which is the local host address.

00:48:49.971 --> 00:48:53.771
So I'm now listening to a port on my own computer.

00:48:53.771 --> 00:48:55.930
And this is the port that the tunnel

00:48:55.930 --> 00:48:58.611
is going to be opened on.

00:48:58.971 --> 00:49:03.971
I can then create this SSH configuration.

00:49:06.771 --> 00:49:11.771
And again, I can connect to this address

00:49:13.171 --> 00:49:17.211
is 192.168.0.101.

00:49:17.211 --> 00:49:20.250
And I actually need to use this port

00:49:20.250 --> 00:49:22.091
because that's how I've configured.

00:49:22.091 --> 00:49:24.531
So I'm just going to connect to this port.

00:49:24.531 --> 00:49:26.890
And I'm going to use this port

00:49:26.890 --> 00:49:29.450
because that's how I've configured that.

00:49:29.450 --> 00:49:34.211
And I just need to specify this argument,

00:49:34.211 --> 00:49:37.091
which is tunnel equals true, okay?

00:49:39.010 --> 00:49:44.010
And then if I try and launch now using this configuration,

00:49:50.450 --> 00:49:54.570
this should now hopefully work.

00:49:54.570 --> 00:49:58.171
So yay, now I have two workers

00:49:58.171 --> 00:50:02.091
and they are on another machine that I have

00:50:02.091 --> 00:50:03.411
that's in London.

00:50:03.411 --> 00:50:07.771
It's actually a very old sort of converted Mac mini,

00:50:07.771 --> 00:50:10.890
actually, but it's running Linux now.

00:50:10.890 --> 00:50:13.611
And to prove to you that it's running Linux,

00:50:13.611 --> 00:50:16.330
I'm going to run like Mirai,

00:50:16.330 --> 00:50:20.091
and I'm just going to ask for the sys.info, okay?

00:50:21.051 --> 00:50:25.651
From the worker, and you can see that,

00:50:25.651 --> 00:50:27.411
hey, this is running Linux.

00:50:27.411 --> 00:50:29.411
And just to prove I'm not running Linux,

00:50:32.330 --> 00:50:34.930
this is my machine.

00:50:34.930 --> 00:50:38.051
It's definitely some form of Mac.

00:50:39.330 --> 00:50:43.171
Okay, that was a whirlwind, but if you got that,

00:50:43.171 --> 00:50:46.490
you'll understand how sort of SSH timing.

00:50:46.490 --> 00:50:48.411
But as you can see,

00:50:48.890 --> 00:50:51.810
all you had to do was create this configuration,

00:50:51.810 --> 00:50:53.250
which is just this URL,

00:50:53.250 --> 00:50:57.370
which is if you can access that machine over SSH,

00:50:57.370 --> 00:51:02.370
you have all the information you need to run Mirai over SSH.

00:51:04.971 --> 00:51:09.651
Okay, Charlie, this was so much information all at one time.

