00:51:21.411 --> 00:51:23.810
I believe NumPy distributes calculations

00:51:23.810 --> 00:51:24.851
over multiple cores.

00:51:24.851 --> 00:51:28.411
So does Mirai allow R to perform the same thing as well?

00:51:29.611 --> 00:51:30.531
Yes, it does.

00:51:30.531 --> 00:51:34.731
And the NumPy is very specific.

00:51:34.731 --> 00:51:39.731
So it will run only numerical work that NumPy handles.

00:51:40.731 --> 00:51:45.731
Mirai allows you to run arbitrary R expressions.

00:51:46.570 --> 00:51:49.531
So anything you can do in R, you can put in Mirai.

00:51:49.531 --> 00:51:51.330
That's the difference.

00:51:51.330 --> 00:51:52.611
Great, any R processes.

